In Task 1 of my Digital Literacy project, I created an infographic to spread awareness about the importance of digital literacy among students. I used Canva, which is an easy and user-friendly online design tool, to design my infographic. The aim of this task was to present important information in a clear, simple, and visually attractive way.

My infographic covers key topics such as the definition of digital literacy, safe internet practices, useful digital tools for students, and basic email etiquette. I used bullet points, icons, and different colors to make the content easy to read and understand. The design helps students learn how to use digital platforms effectively, stay safe while using the internet, and communicate professionally in an online environment.

After completing the infographic, I downloaded it and uploaded it to my GitHub repository in the “task-1-presentation” folder. This step helped me understand how to manage and organize files on GitHub.

While working on this task, I found it interesting to explore different templates and design features in Canva. However, selecting the best layout and arranging the content properly was slightly challenging. Overall, this task improved my creativity, presentation skills, and understanding of digital literacy.


✅ Why this is perfect:

